ded the excellent work done so far in the state and made some recommendations for improvement. The Executive Secretary, State Primary Healthcare Development Agency, Dr Abimbola Folohunsho, appreciated the present administration on the revolutionary change being experienced in the agency. VANGUARD The African Regional Certification Centre on Thursday disclosed that Nigeria would soon be declared polio-free by June 2020. Mr Anad Dumba, the Team leader, African Regional Satisfaction Committee, stated this in Ilorin while conducting delegates round the Kwara Ministry of Health. Dumba stated that the delegates are in the state… March 5, 2020 In "Health" Dr Faisal Shuaib, the Executive Director, National Primary Healthcare Development Agency (NPHCDA) has expressed optimism that Nigeria will be declared polio-free by 2020. December 10, 2019 In "News" Africa is set to be declared polio-free as Nigeria marks three years without recording a single case of polio infection, thus moving a step closer towards polio-free certification by the World Health Organisation, WHO, in early 2020. August 24, 2019 In "Health"